  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dda\u0dc1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0d9f\u0dba\u0d9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Railway tickets are in short supply due to increased demand",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Due to the fuel crisis, bus fares have risen excessively and bus runs have decreased, with the increase in demand for trains, railway station officials say that train tickets are running out.",
        "Due to this, the issuance of regular tickets at many railway stations has become a crisis situation, they say.",
        "Station officials also say that problems are arising due to the exhaustion of regular tickets at railway stations such as Colombo Fort, Maradana, Gampaha, Ragama and many sub-stations."
      ],
